Argentina Wheat Crop to Fall This Year, Exports Drop, USDA Says

-- B y   J e f f   W i l s o n
-- 
2011-04-06T19:15:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/argentina-wheat-crop-to-fall-this-year-exports-drop-usda-says.html
Argentina ’s wheat production may
fall to 13 million metric tons in the year that begins Dec. 1,
down from an estimated 15 million this year, a unit of the  U.S.
Department of Agriculture  said in a  report  posted today on its
website.  Wheat exports may drop to 7.2 million tons next year, down
from an estimated 8.6 million in the year ending Nov. 30, the
USDA’s  Foreign Agricultural Service  said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Wilson in Chicago at 
 jwilson29@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net . 